Ulrich





Member sinceFebruary, 2003
From: Guelph, Ontario                                         

                                        3,380 posts
                                    







                                Posted by Ulrich 
                                on Thursday, February 21, 2013 10:57 PM
                            


The glory days didn't die with steam. Stand at trackside today and tell me what you see isn't at least as impressive as what was commonplace in the 50s. Steam was good in its day. Today's ES4400CWs are every bit as impressive as the Berkshires and Moguls  of a bygone era. The trains are bigger today... the systems are more complex. We are moving far more freight with far fewer people than was accomplished 50 or 70 years ago. EHH has it right, railroading is  above and foremost a business.  Running steam locomotives and excursions are an expense and get in the way of production. Perhaps the right answer is to have museums and fan groups come up with a rail line of their own that could be used for the express purpose of running steam locomotives and vintage rail equipment.  Maybe a short line could be revitalized and run with steam power.
 
 






Reply



























